article.description: — Ryan Rollins had 25 points as Toledo beat Ohio 87-69 on Friday night.
article.headline: Rollins scores 25 to lift Toledo past Ohio 87-69
article.linkText: Rollins scores 25 to lift Toledo past Ohio 87-69
article.story: ATHENS, Ohio -- — Ryan Rollins had 25 points as Toledo beat Ohio 87-69 on Friday night. RayJ Dennis had 18 points for Toledo (15-4, 7-1 Mid-American Conference), which won its sixth straight game. Setric Millner Jr. added 17 points. JT Shumate had 13 points. Jason Carter had 19 points for the Bobcats (14-3, 5-1), whose nine-game winning streak ended. Mark Sears added 14 points. Ben Vander Plas had 12 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
